              "id": "1777360516473_1",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "You are given a JSON object containing employee termination records.\n\nInput JSON:\n {{$context.$nodes.EXECUTING_SQL_QUERY.$output}} \n\nTask:\nExtract and aggregate the data by manager and department.\n\nRules:\n1. Use \"Manager Display Name\" as the manager name.\n2. Use \"Department Name\" as the department.\n3. Count the number of termination records for each unique manager + department combination.\n4. If \"Termination Headcount\" exists, sum it instead of simply counting rows.\n5. Return only valid JSON.\n6. Do not include explanations, markdown, or extra text.\n\nOutput format:\n[\n  {\n    \"managerName\": \"string\",\n    \"department\": \"string\",\n    \"count\": number\n  }\n]"
            }
